snippet.textDisplay: Who the hell would buy this stupid thing. Screen doesn't even seem to open fully flat & how much opening & closing is that joint going to handle until it starts to crack or degrade the main screen. Ridiculous. If you're going to implement a folding screen do it in a device that gives you the option to open into a larger tablet sized screen. What would be cool is a large phone that's 3"W X 6"H with a second 3 panel folding screen that gives you a 9" X 6" tablet. Then you'd have a phone & tablet in one. That's where this folding screen technology would make sense. The problem with the larger phones now that do fold in half is you essentially end up with a square device when opened so you lose the aspect ratio for videos.
